Package frogger.util

Enum GameManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<GameManager>
      • frogger.util.GameManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<GameManager>
    public enum GameManager
extends java.lang.Enum<GameManager>

    GameManager

    A GameManager is an object of utility to manage the game status and events globally, and update view of game.

    This class is implemented as Enum for singleton.

    Usage: 

        GameManager.INSTANCE.{METHOD}()
    Since:
    0.2
    See Also:
    Map, GameController, GameStatus

      • initInfo

        private void initInfo()
        Initialize(reset) classes related to information, including Life, Time and Score.

        For Life, reset value of life to default.

        For Time, reset remaining seconds in time to 60.

        For Score, reset currentScore to 0 and get highestScore from ScoreManager

        See Also:
        life, time, currentScore, highestScore

      • checkWin

        private boolean checkWin()
        Tests if player win this level.
        Returns:
        boolean for whether all End have frog.

      • winGame

        private void winGame()
        Player wins the game.

        Adds point of 1000 to currentScore and update to game view.

        Calls GameController.activateWinIndicator() to activate indicator.

        Calls endGame() to end game.

      • loseGame

        private void loseGame()
        Player loses the game.

        Calls GameController.activateWinIndicator() to activate indicator.

        Calls endGame() to end game.

      • endGame

        private void endGame()
        Ends current game.

        Play end music by calling ThemePlayer.themeMusicFactory(String).

        Set gameStatus to END and call updateAnimationStatus() pause Animations.

        Reset time.

        Call ScoreManager.update() to save score.

      • handleLogTurtleTouched

        public void handleLogTurtleTouched​(SelfMovable selfMovable)
        Called when frog is touching a log or turtle.

        Moves the frog with this log or turtle.

        Parameters:
        selfMovable - the SelfMovable which is touching frog.

      • handleCarTouched

        public void handleCarTouched()
        Called when frog is touching a car.

        set drop death to frog by calling handleFrogDie(Death)

      • handleSunkWetTurtleTouched

        public void handleSunkWetTurtleTouched()
        Called when frog is touching a sunk wet turtle.

        set drop death to frog by calling handleFrogDie(Death)

      • handleEndTouched

        public void handleEndTouched​(End end)
        Called when a frog is touching end.

        Set End to a frog exist status.

        Add 200 points by calling Score.gain(int) and update to game view.

        checkWin() and send frog to home if not.

        Reset time, Frog.resetyPosSmallest() and frog itself.

        Parameters:
        end - the end touched
        See Also:
        End

      • handleFrogDie

        public void handleFrogDie​(Death death)
        Called when there are events causing death of frog.

        Set frog to dead by Frog.setDeath(Death), play corresponding effect music and decrease life and score. After death, play REBORN effect sound.

        Parameters:
        death - the death type to be set

      • handleFrogJumpUp

        public void handleFrogJumpUp()
        Called when a frog jump to up direction.

        If frog is jump to right area, update high bound and increase score.

      • handleFrogInWater

        public void handleFrogInWater()
        Called when current frog is in water area.

        Iterate all elements in water area, if no element is touching, set frog to death.

      • handleTimeUpdate

        public void handleTimeUpdate​(int secondsLeft)
        Called once every second during game period by {link @Time}.

        When game is not end, call GameController.deactivateTimeIndicator() or EffectPlayer.effectMusicFactory(String) at specific time.

        When game is end, call switchBack() when 7 seconds past.

        Parameters:
        secondsLeft - seconds left for this round of game

      • switchBack

        private void switchBack()
        Switch back to home screen and pop up score board.
        See Also:
        SceneSwitch.switchToGame(String), SceneSwitch.showScoreBoard()
